<h1>Problem 1251 - 2022 Israel TST10 P2 of 3</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Let \(f: \mathbb{Z}^2\to \mathbb{R}\) be a function.  It is known that for any integer \(C\) the four functions of \(x\) \[f(x,C), \quad f(C,x),\quad f(x, C+x), \quad f(x,C-x)\] are polynomials of degree at most \(100\). Prove that \(f\) is equal to a polynomial in two variables \(x,y\), and find its maximum possible degree.</p>
<p><i>Remark: The degree of a bivariate polynomial \(P(x,y)\) is defined as the maximal value of \(i+j\) over all monomials \(x^iy^j\) appearing in \(P\) with a non-zero coefficient.</i></p>
